Factorial : 
Input: 
import java.util.*;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Functions {

public static void factorial(int n){
     if(n < 0) {
       System.out.println("Invaild Number");
        return;
    }
     int fact = 1;
     for( int i=n; i>=1; i--){
        fact = fact*i;
     }

     System.out.println(fact);
     return;
 }

public static void main(String[] args) {
     Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
     int a = sc.nextInt();
      factorial(a);
 }
    
}

Output: 
5
120
-5
Invaild Number

Average of Three Numbers:
Input:
import java.util.*;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Functions {
    public static int average( int a, int b, int c) { 
        int avg = (a + b + c) / 3;
        return avg;
    }
 public static void main(String[] args) {
     Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
     int a = sc.nextInt();
     int b = sc.nextInt();
     int c = sc.nextInt();
     int avg = average(a, b, c);
    System.out.println("Average of Three Numbers: " + avg);
   
 }
    
}

Output:
5
5
5
Average of Three Numbers: 5


Greater Number : 
Input:
import java.util.*;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Functions {
    public static int greater( int a, int b){
        if ( a > b){
            return a;
        }
        else {
            return b;
        }
    }
 public static void main(String[] args) {
     Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
     int a = sc.nextInt();
     int b = sc.nextInt();
     int greater = greater(a, b);
    
    System.out.println("Greater Number : " + greater);
   
 }
    
}

Output:
5
6
Greater Number : 6
6
5
Greater Number : 6

A function to print the sum of all odd numbers from 1 to n:
Input:
import java.util.*;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Functions {
    public static int oddsum(int n){
        int sum = 0;
        for( int i = 1 ; i<=n; i++){
            if(i%2 != 0){
                System.out.println("Odd Number : " + i);
                sum = sum + i;
            }
        }
        return sum;
    }
 public static void main(String[] args) {
     Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
     int a = sc.nextInt();
    int sum = oddsum(a);
    
    System.out.println("Sum of Odd Numbers : " + sum);
   
 }
    
}

Output:
10
Odd Number : 1
Odd Number : 3
Odd Number : 5
Odd Number : 7
Odd Number : 9
Sum of Odd Numbers : 25

20
Odd Number : 1
Odd Number : 3
Odd Number : 5
Odd Number : 7
Odd Number : 9
Odd Number : 11
Odd Number : 13
Odd Number : 15
Odd Number : 17
Odd Number : 19
Sum of Odd Numbers : 100

A function that takes in the radius as input and returns the circumference of a circle:
Input:
import java.util.*;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Functions {
    public static double circleCircumference(double n){
        double cir = 2 * 3.14 * n;
        return cir;
    }
 public static void main(String[] args) {
     Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
     double a = sc.nextDouble();
    double cir = circleCircumference(a);
    
    System.out.println("Sum of Odd Numbers : " + cir);
   
 }
    
}

Output :
6
Sum of Odd Numbers : 37.68

























